HEADWORD: Luxurious
<hw>Lux*u"ri*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>luxuriosus</ets>: cf. F. <ets>luxurieux</ets>. See
<er>Luxury</er>.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to luxury; ministering to
luxury; supplied with the conditions of luxury; <as>as, a
<ex>luxurious</ex> life; a <ex>luxurious</ex> table; <ex>luxurious</ex>
ease.</as></def> ⟦ldquo⟧ <xex>Luxurious</xex> cities. ⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Lux*u"ri*ous*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Lux*u"ri*ous*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

